From: stopless-java-gc <noreply@anthropic.com>
Subject: [PATCH 0038/N] flags-cflags.m4 + buildjdk-spec: --undefined-version for TARGET only

The HotSpot mapfile (`make/hotspot/lib/JvmMapfile.gmk` →
`mapfile-vers`) lists vtables for many function-local closure
classes — e.g.,
  _ZTVZN15G1RemSetSummary6updateEvE11CollectData
  _ZTVZN18G1ConcurrentRefine30get_and_reset_refinement_statsEvE12CollectStats
  _ZTVZ21WB_HandshakeWalkStackE16TraceSelfClosure

LLD on FreeBSD/CheriBSD rejects the link with `error: version
script assignment of 'SUNWprivate_1.1' to symbol ... failed:
symbol not defined` when the corresponding object files don't
actually emit those vtables. clang's DCE elides those vtables
for closures whose virtual dispatch isn't kept.

GNU ld and macOS lld accept the version script when listed
symbols are missing; FreeBSD/LLD does not by default. Add
`-Wl,--undefined-version` for `OPENJDK_TARGET_OS=bsd` in
`flags-cflags.m4`.

`SET_SHARED_LIBRARY_MAPFILE` is shared between BUILD and TARGET
passes — but the BUILD pass uses host GNU ld 2.38, which only
supports the negative `--no-undefined-version` (not the new
positive `--undefined-version` form added in 2.40+). Override
`SET_SHARED_LIBRARY_MAPFILE` in `buildjdk-spec.gmk.in` so the
BUILD pass uses just `-Wl,-version-script=` without the bsd flag.

Same shape as 0013 (override EXTRA_*FLAGS for buildjdk).

Refs: docs/05_zgc_cheri_collision_report.md §6 (patch 0038)

--- a/make/autoconf/flags-cflags.m4
+++ b/make/autoconf/flags-cflags.m4
@@ -64,6 +64,11 @@ AC_DEFUN([FLAGS_SETUP_SHARED_LIBS],
       SET_SHARED_LIBRARY_NAME='-Wl,-soname=[$]1'
       SET_SHARED_LIBRARY_MAPFILE='-Wl,-version-script=[$]1'

+      if test "x$OPENJDK_TARGET_OS" = xbsd; then
+        # LLD on FreeBSD/CheriBSD errors out when version-script lists symbols
+        # the object files don't define; downgrade to a warning.
+        SET_SHARED_LIBRARY_MAPFILE="$SET_SHARED_LIBRARY_MAPFILE -Wl,--undefined-version"
+      fi
       # arm specific settings
       if test "x$OPENJDK_TARGET_CPU" = "xarm"; then
         # '-Wl,-z,origin' isn't used on arm.
--- a/make/autoconf/buildjdk-spec.gmk.in
+++ b/make/autoconf/buildjdk-spec.gmk.in
@@ -104,3 +104,7 @@
 override EXTRA_CXXFLAGS :=
 override EXTRA_LDFLAGS :=
 override EXTRA_ASFLAGS :=
+
+# Strip the bsd-target --undefined-version LLD flag for the BUILD pass:
+# host GNU ld 2.38 doesn't recognize it (added in binutils 2.40).
+override SET_SHARED_LIBRARY_MAPFILE = -Wl,-version-script=$1
